    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-22T01:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-22T01:36:00-05:00" n="986"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d986">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.Os4/121.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-22T00:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1914, midnight</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Having been handed my passports at 7.30 tonight, will leave tomorrow night or
                    Friday morning. What about Counsel General Shanklin and other consular officers?
                    Please instruct immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
